('3b59ad83-8274-4a6d-8ba2-19ae9ceb4192', '55b66aa2-631f-4d58-9144-477cc4c3aed2', '2a514bf5-beed-4b0b-9ca6-3e8b570e8fb6', 'Faced with this, this person leans into the move, adding exposure where others are flinching and betting on the reversal, and true to form expects to be the exception to a risk it can otherwise describe accurately.', 'Breaks the decision into weighted criteria before looking at gut feel, and lets the tally overrule any single strong reaction. Price action does not care which argument feels more convincing.', 'A noticeable but manageable spike of unease, resolving into defiant doubling — that settles once the choice is made.', 0.67, 'c09637e6-6320-47d7-8d8f-6c374ac2b3fb'),
('ce9395fa-8c33-460c-bb6a-12493da535bd', '3e36b05d-edc1-4b9b-99a1-1bfed3a9f8bb', '72586ce9-4b83-4ac3-a3c8-c0efbc9df588', 'Faced with this, this type leans into the move, adding exposure where others are flinching and betting on the reversal, and true to form adopts a conviction mainly because the room already has.', 'Treats the choice as a small research problem: gather the knowable facts first, model the downside, then commit only once the math stops moving. Price action does not care which argument feels more convincing.', 'A flash of heat that cools almost immediately, resolving into vindication seeking — that fades within the hour once the decision is locked in.', 0.59, 'c09637e6-6320-47d7-8d8f-6c374ac2b3fb'),
('b912e918-696e-4390-89dd-6820280c7e03', '5e6caac5-9ffd-4db7-a796-30f55f4f5947', 'be0ed835-4651-4f9c-a1ea-1452ca7f3fea', 'Faced with this, the individual executes the pre-committed plan exactly, resisting the urge to improvise under pressure, and true to form never quite escapes the first figure it heard, however arbitrary.', 'Distrusts the first plausible-sounding answer and keeps testing alternatives until one survives every objection raised against it. This time the variable is money moving in real time.', 'A noticeable but manageable spike of unease, resolving into vindication seeking — that settles once the choice is made.', 0.69, 'c09637e6-6320-47d7-8d8f-6c374ac2b3fb'),
('bb02c2aa-706b-410c-a2f8-999dc3db9810', 'c4071f1a-e814-42cc-b248-609d6e3b0ec3', 'be0ed835-4651-4f9c-a1ea-1452ca7f3fea', 'Faced with this, this person acts on the first strong feeling, hitting the button before the reasoning fully forms, and true to form locks in small wins fast and rides large losses far past the point of sense.', 'Keeps every option notionally open as long as possible, even at the cost of the best ones expiring first. This time the variable is money moving in real time.', 'An immediate jolt of alarm, resolving into fomo buying — that keeps resurfacing in quiet moments for days afterward.', 0.54, 'c09637e6-6320-47d7-8d8f-6c374ac2b3fb'),
('89116ead-ecbb-4ce7-b28b-213873bffe31', 'e52c6611-bc16-43c1-9acc-43875ed73cd4', '1e219e15-676b-4f12-a68a-7914dc965226', 'Faced with this, this type scales in aggressively, judging the crowd''s fear as the better signal to fade, and true to form jumps into whatever everyone else already seems to be winning at.', 'Feels the decision settle before it is fully articulated, and moves on that settling rather than waiting for certainty. Price action does not care which argument feels more convincing.', 'A noticeable but manageable spike of unease, resolving into defiant doubling — that settles once the choice is made.', 0.53, 'c09637e6-6320-47d7-8d8f-6c374ac2b3fb'),
('6e148447-59c3-477a-bfda-7b1a2b7683b8', 'bd800ac2-e43c-4897-b171-fffb68457178', 'cbd05e75-9567-418c-ab4b-2369323703ee', 'Faced with this, the individual leans into the move, adding exposure where others are flinching and betting on the reversal, and true to form is most certain precisely where their competence is thinnest.', 'Recognizes the shape of the situation from past experience before consciously naming why, then acts on that recognition. This time the variable is money moving in real time.', 'A noticeable but manageable spike of unease, resolving into righteous anger — that settles once the choice is made.', 0.55, 'c09637e6-6320-47d7-8d8f-6c374ac2b3fb'),
('f364007e-65c3-4694-bd1d-501676dc9c27', 'bd1f8560-0e43-4546-989f-53b775b21f7e', '55b4b68e-8f95-4365-9509-aecebf6cb4b8', 'Faced with this, this profile reacts to the headline before confirming it, then scrambles to justify the trade after, and true to form cannot watch a rally from the sidelines for long.', 'Commits fast to end the tension, treating a quick wrong move as better than a slow right one. Price action does not care which argument feels more convincing.', 'A rush of adrenaline that narrows focus fast, resolving into paralysis — that gets relived and replayed long after it stops being useful.', 0.5, 'c09637e6-6320-47d7-8d8f-6c374ac2b3fb'),
('45c9abc7-c605-48ec-8e0b-00483a557191', '5f5f4036-39a0-4d46-bfac-6409903a2b62', '6733ee11-e30c-4c63-980f-45f0a80d916d', 'Faced with this, the individual presses the position further, treating the volatility itself as the opportunity, and true to form takes the crowd''s confidence as a substitute for its own analysis.', 'Reads the situation in a single gut pass, locks onto the option that "feels" right, and assembles the justification afterward. The numbers on the screen are the only feedback that matters here.', 'A noticeable but manageable spike of unease, resolving into aggressive counter — that dissolves quickly once the ambiguity clears.', 0.54, 'c09637e6-6320-47d7-8d8f-6c374ac2b3fb')
